The wall and Mr. Dependable!!
The man whom I used to admire for his stubbornness to stay on the ground till end. He was the only batsman who used to build pressure on bowlers not through his fours and sixes, but through his dot balls. Who made girls admire for his innocent looks. He was my crush and my classmates in school used to tease me for admiring him. People often used to compare him with Sachin. I still don't understand those people. Kohli's decision back-fires as South Africa achieve series parity

After Virat Kohli opted to bat stressing that batting first is one of the areas India are "looking to strengthen", the home team's innings was a tale of two halves. In the first 10 overs, it was all positive batting as they managed 76 runs and weren't worried about wickets going down considering their long batting line-up as a cushion. But South Africa came back strongly in the second half of the innings, capitalising on a sluggish pitch that was also gripping a bit, as they gave away only 58 runs while picking up six wickets to restrict India to 134 for 9.

Quinton de Kock then led South Africa's reply, striking an unbeaten 79 off 52, which included five sixes and six fours, and was involved in half-century stands to help complete the chase as early as the 17th over with nine wickets in hand to achieve series parity with a clinical all-round performance.
